<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/9647ff7e152eff9ae6d5557f764e970f.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 5 and c = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.2</li><li>38.7</li><li>51.3</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}^{{2}}={5}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}={25}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}-{25}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{39}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{39}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.2449979983984}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.2}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{5}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{38.682187453489}\approx{38.7}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{5}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{51.317812546511}\approx{51.3}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

